article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- — Marquel Sutton had 25 points in Omaha's 79-76 win over Stetson on Thursday night. Sutton added 10 rebounds for the Mavericks (2-0). Lance Waddles added 15 points while shooting 5 for 17, including 3 for 9 from beyond the arc while they also had eight rebounds. Ja'Sean Glover had nine points and shot 3 of 5 from the field and 3 of 3 from the free-throw line. The Hatters (1-1) were led by Jamie Phillips Jr., who recorded 18 points, five assists and two steals. Jordan Wood added 15 points and three blocks for Stetson. Abramo Canka had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
